  <heading>LASTB (SIMD&amp;FP scalar)</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Extract last element to SIMD&amp;FP scalar register</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction extracts the Last active element to a SIMD&amp;FP scalar register.
If there is an Active element, the
 Last active element
 from the final source vector register is extracted.
If there are no Active elements,
the highest-numbered element is extracted.
Then the extracted element is  placed
in the destination SIMD&amp;FP register.</para>
    </authored>
    <predicated>True</predicated>
  </desc>
